column4:
Last night, I had the incredible honor of paying tribute to one of our greatest Americans, Congressman John Lewis.  Unfortunately, it was too long for Twitter.

Please take a moment to watch it on my Facebook page, @DonaldPayneJr, and pass it on.
@repjohnlewis https://t.co/D4jAlMQfA3

I wanted to thank Rep. Nita Lowey for all her service to the people of NY-17 and our country.

The Chair of the House Appropriations Committee will retire this year after 30 years on the committee and 16 Congressional terms.  I wish her the best.
@RepLowey https://t.co/vpjaoR9jzE

Great to hear that 17 organizations in my district were awarded some of the first grants from the New Jersey Pandemic Relief Fund.  Thanks to New Jersey's First Lady Tammy Murphy for creating it.  

For more information, visit https://t.co/dmHuB9NKtg
@njprf https://t.co/Ye6digwhxw

Rutgers will graduate 192 qualified medical students early and Gov. Murphy will reactivate retired doctors and nurses to help combat coronavirus statewide.   

I'm delighted because our medical heroes need all the help they can get right now.  
@RU.NJMS @governorphilmurphy https://t.co/dyNAE4vMYt

CORONAVIRUS UPDATE:

Proud to hear the VA Medical Facility in East Orange will make its excess space available to coronavirus patients and they will do it in a way that won't threaten the veterans there with infection.  
@VeteransAffairs https://t.co/vaL6J1h1vO

I really enjoyed the small business webinar that Newark Mayor Ras Baraka organized today.  It was great to be a part of an event that will help so many small businesses get the resources and financial assistance they need during this economic crisis.
@CityofNewarkNJ  
@rasjbaraka https://t.co/H2Q6Fu3hBX

March is National Colorectal Cancer Awareness Month.  Encourage loved ones older than 45 to get screened.  Actor Will Smith's routine screening allowed doctors to find and remove cancerous polyps.
I spoke about it on the House floor today.  
@FightCRC @ColorectalCancerAlliance https://t.co/YKQ3bfgIcz

Denise Wilkerson is the Council President for the City of Roselle, New Jersey, but her dedication to her community extends far beyond her city council work.

I praised her on the floor of the House yesterday. 
@officialRoselleNJ https://t.co/f7t471SdGk

Today, Speaker Pelosi renamed the Oversight Committee room in honor of the late Rep. Elijah Cummings.  

It is a well-deserved honor for my former "Father on the (House) Floor." 

@SpeakerPelosi @OversightDems @RepCummings

@j_nothdurft @TheNJGlobe @NKF_Advocacy Jason- Thanks for your understanding.  As you figured, I had the flu and the doctor told me not to attend to avoid spreading it.  I put out a press release about it yesterday for everyone to see.   

Check under "Press Releases" at https://t.co/AbhjA2O8sG.

Happy Valentine's Day!
